        <h3>2.Weight Management </h3>
        <p>Exercise helps in controlling weight, which is vital in managing chronic conditions like diabetes, arthritis, and heart disease.<br /> Maintaining a healthy weight can improve overall health and reduce the severity of symptoms</p>
        <h4>3.Enhanced Respiratory Function</h4>
        <p>For conditions like asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), exercise can improve lung capacity and make breathing easier.</p>
        <h5>4.Better Blood Sugar Controlt</h5>
        <p>Physical activity helps in regulating blood sugar levels, which is critical for managing diabetes. Exercise increases insulin sensitivity, allowing the body to use glucose more effectively</p>
